<item>
            <title>[KARAF-1986] instance.properties file doesn&apos;t get updated if karaf.name is changed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KARAF-1986</link>
                <project id="12311140" key="KARAF">Karaf</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;By default, the root Karaf instance is named &quot;root&quot; and after startup this appears in instances/instance.properties as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;item.0.name=root&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now, if karaf.name is later changed, this file never gets updated with the new name. The only way currently to get instance.properties up to date, is to delete the file so it is regenerated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
